Cargo.lock is the dependency lock file for a Rust project containing seven local workspace crates (ctx-brief, ctx-cage, ctx-context, ctx-core, ctx-scan, ctx-status, ctx-summarize, ctx-verify) and their transitive dependencies pinned to specific versions.

The file freezes all crate versions to ensure reproducible builds. Do not edit by hand; Cargo regenerates it from Cargo.toml changes. Key transitive dependencies: serde/serde_json for serialization across multiple crates, clap 4.6.1 for CLI parsing in all user-facing binaries, thiserror 2.0.18 for error handling, sha2 0.10.9 (in ctx-core), and ignore 0.4.27 (in ctx-scan and ctx-summarize) for file traversal with .gitignore support. The nix and rustix crates appear only in ctx-cage for POSIX system calls.